# Reverse Seared Ribeye Steak

> #beef #fancy

- Steak | Ribeye, 1 1/2 - 2” thick | 
- Salt | to taste | 
- Black Pepper | to taste | 

Season steaks generously with salt and pepper and rest on a rack placed over a baking sheet for 30 minutes.

Preheat oven to 225.

Place steaks in oven on wire rack and cook until internal temp reaches 115 degrees. Approximately 30 minutes.

> By adjusting the oven temp to as low as 175 degrees during cooking, you can slow down or speed up the cooking process.

- Vegetable Oil |  | 

Place stainless steel pan over high heat until screaming hot. Coat with oil.

Sear steaks on both sides and sear edges. On larger sides, let steak sit for about a minute to brown well.
